An agricultural production process involving wild plants, insects or other organisms that are tended and protected.
A planned process involving the rearing, manufacture or distribution of food material.
The cultivation of plants for food.
Open-air plant cultivation using non-organic fertilizer, pest and weed control treatments.
Conventional outdoor/open-air plant cultivation includes ICMS (Integrated Crop Management Systems)
The organic cultivation of plants in an unsheltered area.
The organic cultivation of plants in a sheltered area.
A method of growing plants, usually crops, without soil, by using mineral nutrient solutions in an aqueous solvent.
A food object quality which describes the integrity of the medium in which the food is packed for preservation and handling or the medium surrounding foods.

Previous definition: It is important to distinguish whether the food in question has been drained or not drained when evaluating the nutrient content.
Related term to PRESENCE OF PACKING MEDIUM is K.  PACKING MEDIUM.
A food object quality where the medium in which the food is packed is drained.
LanguaL curation note: Used to indicate that the food, for example a canned food, is drained.
